comments: Bledsoe is a good teacher. she can get distracted easily if you want a discussional tangent to help with the sometimes dry material. Her tests are not easy, many questions from the book material. make sure you at least skim the chapters before the tests for the side note info that is not in the ppt\'s. Shes not bad on the eyes either ;-)
Overall a good course. However, she can be a little bit cloudy with the information. Gets distracted easily. But extremely nice and willing to help out.
she taught us great on topics - especially ecg\'s. we were top in our training programs in this because of her.
Wonderful teacher. Very helpful especially about giving you hints about what to study for tests.
